Description: Defines the root of an HTML document.
Contains meta-information about the document, such as the title and links to stylesheets.
Specifies the title of the webpage (appears in the browser tab).
Contains the main content of the webpage.
Heading elements, where <h1> is the largest heading and <h6> is the smallest.
Defines a division or section of content, often used for grouping.
Defines a small section of content, often used for styling part of a text.
Defines a list item in an ordered or unordered list.
Defines a form for user input.
Defines an input field (e.g., text box, radio button, etc.).
Embeds another HTML page within the current page.
Defines metadata like character set, author, or viewport information.
Defines CSS styles for the document.
